<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1034,1959]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Head and thorax greenish yellow. Crown of vertex with two small light brown spots near apex, two squarish light brown patches one on either side of coronal sulcus behind transverse furrow touching inner margin of eye. Face pale brown. Eyes dark brown with greenish yellow tinge. Pronotum mottled with dark brown patches on disc. Basal triangles of scutum light brown. Forewings with distinct median spot having dark brown margin on anterior half, lateral large elongate spot and posterior corner.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="111" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1034,1959]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis box="[199,371,1214,1239]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">
<collectingCountry box="[199,257,1214,1239]" name="Malta" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Male</collectingCountry>
genitalia.
</emphasis>
Pygofer in lateral view longer than its height, posterior margin conically rounded, macrosetae confined to posterior half. Valve approximately 
<number box="[687,722,1250,1275]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" value="2.5">2.5</number>
times as wide as long. Subgenital plate with terminal fingerlike process 
<number box="[244,293,1287,1311]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" value="0.33">0.33</number>
as long as total length. Style abruptly narrowed in middle, approximately thrice as long as wide at base, preapical lobe fairly well developed with a few hairlike setae, apophysis stout and blunt. Connective with stem stout and truncate posteriorly, arms bulged and longer than stem. Aedeagus without basal processes, shafts directed posterodorsally, divergent in posterior view, each shaft with short, stout, fingerlike process at apex, abruptly turned anteriorly, 
<taxonomicName box="[451,560,1430,1455]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Amaranthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triangular">triangular</taxonomicName>
lamellate expansion on lateral margin near midlength; gonopore subapical.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1034,1959]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis box="[199,397,1466,1491]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Female seventh sternite 
<number box="[674,709,1467,1491]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" value="3.2">3.2</number>
times as broad at base as long medially, posterior margin sinuate with troughlike excavation medially, posterolateral angles conically rounded. First pair of valvulae broadened slightly beyond base and then narrowed. Second pair of valvulae with irregular teeth, some without secondary dentition on dorsoapical margin, ventroapical margin serrated.
</paragraph>
