<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="111" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1034,1959]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1754,1779]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[326,466,1754,1779]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gillespiei">
<emphasis box="[326,466,1754,1779]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">H. gillespiei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from the 
<typeStatus box="[763,861,1754,1779]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">holotype</typeStatus>
male and one male 
<typeStatus box="[1106,1203,1755,1779]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">paratype</typeStatus>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1280,1380,1754,1779]" name="Thailand" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Thailand</collectingCountry>
(not examined). It is recorded here for the first time from 
<collectingCountry box="[779,840,1790,1815]" name="India" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">India</collectingCountry>
. This species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Okada" authorityName="Okada" box="[1128,1303,1790,1815]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="araii">
<emphasis box="[1128,1219,1791,1814]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">H. araii</emphasis>
Okada
</taxonomicName>
but can be distinguished by the robust stem and arms of the connective, stout and laterally directed apophysis of style, and by the aedeagal shaft with blunt, anteriorly strongly curved fingerlike apical process. Externally it resembles the sympatric species, 
<taxonomicName box="[363,468,1898,1923]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thapai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[363,468,1898,1923]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">H. thapai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[475,564,1898,1923]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[475,564,1898,1923]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
in coloration and can be recognised by the anterior margin of the median spot on the forewing dark brown, and the female seventh sternite with the posterior margin medially broadly excavated.
</paragraph>
